title: TypeError: shap_values() got multiple values for argument 'ranked_outputs'
body:
Dear Scott,
I have three questions(Actually I have a lot of questions, but I will ask next time...)

Q1. I tried to three inputs(categorical, continuous, text) and one output.

final_model = Model([model1.input, model2.input, model3.input], model_merge_out)
explainer = shap.DeepExplainer(final_model, [X_categorical_npary[0:100], X_continuous_npary[0:100], X_padded_docs[0:100]])
shap_values = explainer.shap_values([X_categorical_test_npary[0:100], X_continuous_test_npary[0:100], padded_docs_test[0:100]])
shap.summary_plot(shap_values, [X_categorical_npary[0:100], X_continuous_npary[0:100], X_padded_docs[0:100]], plot_type="bar")

However, when I ran the last code  I got an error as below

shap.summary_plot(shap_values, [X_categorical_npary[0:100], X_continuous_npary[0:100], X_padded_docs[0:100]], plot_type="bar")
Traceback (most recent call last):

  File "<ipython-input-26-0121926afd66>", line 1, in <module>
    shap.summary_plot(shap_values, [X_categorical_npary[0:100], X_continuous_npary[0:100], X_padded_docs[0:100]], plot_type="bar")

  File "C:\ProgramData\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\shap\plots\summary.py", line 75, in summary_plot
    num_features = (shap_values[0].shape[1] if multi_class else shap_values.shape[1])

AttributeError: 'list' object has no attribute 'shape'

Q2. As above, whenever I run this kinds of multiple inputs model, I should get list type of "shap_values". So, I should convert list to numpy array type, right?


Q3. When I tried to use two inputs as below

final_model12 = Model([model1.input, model2.input], model_merge_out12)
final_model12.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mae', metrics=['mse', 'mae', 'mape'])
history12 = final_model12.fit([X_categorical, X_continuous], Y_los, batch_size=64, epochs= 5 , verbose=1)

explainer_model12 = shap.DeepExplainer(final_model12, [X_categorical_npary[:100], X_continuous_npary[:100]])
shap_values_model12 = explainer_model12.shap_values(X_categorical_test_npary[0:100], X_continuous_test_npary[:100], ranked_outputs=None, output_rank_order='max')
shap.summary_plot(shap_values_model12, [X_categorical_npary[0:100], X_continuous_npary[0:100]], plot_type="bar")

Also, I got an error as below

TypeError: shap_values() got multiple values for argument 'ranked_outputs'

Thank you for your time.
